    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1957-09-23T16:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1957-09-23T16:00:00-05:00" n="260"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d260">
                <head>260. Telegram From the <gloss type="from">Mission at the United
                        Nations</gloss> to the <gloss type="to">Department of State</gloss>
                    <note n="1" type="source" xml:id="d260fn1">Source: Department of State, Central
                        Files, 310.2/9–2357. Official Use Only.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <hi rend="italic">
                            <placeName>New York</placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian"
                                when="1957-09-23T17:00:00-04:00">September 23, 1957—5 p.m.</date>
                        </hi>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <gloss target="#t_DelgaDelGA1">Delga</gloss> 33. Verbatim text. Re <gloss
                        target="#t_UN1">UN</gloss> membership. We propose to discuss following draft
                    resolution on membership Vietnam with <gloss target="#t_UKDel1">UKDel</gloss>
                    and few others with view cosponsorship if <gloss target="#t_Dept1">Dept</gloss>
                    has no objections to it.<note n="2" xml:id="d260fn2">The U.N. General Assembly
                        opened its Twelfth Session on September 17.</note> We doubt whether
                    reference to “veto” will have any adverse effects on voting, but if we find
                    opposition in informal discussions would delete it. <gloss target="#t_res1"
                        >Res</gloss> on Korea on which we will consult at same time, would be
                    identical except for substitution of appropriate resolution numbers and
                    “Republic of Korea”.</p>
                <p>The General Assembly</p>
                <p>Recalling its Resolutions 620 <gloss target="#t_C1">C</gloss> (VII) and 1017 B
                    (XI) finding Vietnam qualified for membership in the United Nations,</p>
                <p>Noting with regret the continued inability of the Security Council to recommend
                    the admission of Vietnam to membership in the United Nations owing to the
                    negative vote of a permanent member of the Security Council,</p>
                <pb facs="0530" n="504" xml:id="pg_504"/>
                <p>Reaffirms that Vietnam is fully qualified for and should be admitted to
                    membership in the United Nations.<note n="3" xml:id="d260fn3">
                        <gloss target="#t_GadelGADel1">Gadel</gloss> 15 to New York, September 25,
                        authorized the delegation to proceed with the procedure suggested in <gloss
                            target="#t_DelgaDelGA1">Delga</gloss> 33. (Department of State, Central
                        Files, 310.2/ 9–2357)</note>
                </p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_LHCJ1">
                            <hi rend="strong">Lodge</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
